HEADWORD: blueweed
<hw>blue"weed</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a coarse prickly European weed
(<spn>Echium vulgare</spn>) with spikes of blue flowers; naturalized in
the U. S.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> blue devil, blue thistle, viper's bugloss.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

